OL,3,CFather and son spared jail for selling
OL,4,Cperegrine falcons in Scottish Borders
OL,6,F"The result in this case is a
OL,7,Ftestament to the collaborative working
OL,8,Fbetween COPFS, Police Scotland, the UK
OL,9,FNational Wildlife Crime Unit (NWCU),
OL,10,Fthe Scottish SPCA and Science and
OL,11,FAdvice for Scottish Agriculture
OL,12,F(SASA)."
OL,14,FDetective Superintendent Bryan Burns
OL,15,Fsaid: "The sale of peregrine falcons
OL,16,Fhas become an extremely lucrative
OL,17,Fbusiness which Timothy and Lewis Hall
OL,18,Fexploited for their own financial gain.
